# {{senseid|en|Q12535449}} Either of two large amounts:
## {{senseid|en|Q16021}} {{lb|en|US|modern British & Australian|short scale}} a [[thousand million]] ({{w|Long and short scales#Comparison|logic: 1,000 × 1,000<sup>2</sup>}}): 1 followed by nine zeros, 10<sup>9</sup>.
##: {{syn|en|milliard<id:Q16021>|thousand million<id:Q16021>}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|title=National Finances
|date=1921-01-24|work=Devon and Exeter Gazette|page=5
|passage=At the last assessment it [the national debt] amounts to seven '''billion''' pounds (£7,000,000,000).}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|title=No hiding place
|date=2013-05-25|volume=407|issue=8837|page=74|magazine=w:The Economist
|url=http://www.economist.com/news/science-and-technology/21578357-plan-assess-peoples-personal-characteristics-their-twitter-streams-no
|passage=In America alone, people spent $170 '''billion''' on “direct marketing”—junk mail of both the physical and electronic varieties—last year. Yet of those who received unsolicited adverts through the post, only 3% bought anything as a result.}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|year=2019|month=October|author=Dan Harvey|title=HS2 costs rise as schedule slips|journal=Modern Railways|page=9|text=However, despite the prospect of HS2 being curtailed and the revelation that the programme is late and '''billions''' over budget, for now, at least, work on the scheme appears to be business as usual}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|author=Reuters|title=Chipmakers look to Japan as worries about China grow|magazine=w:CNN Business|url=https://www.cnn.com/2023/05/18/tech/chipmaking-japan-china-g7|date=2023-05-18|passage=Micron said in a statement that it would bring extreme ultraviolet (EUV) technology to Japan, becoming the first semiconductor company to do so, and expected to invest up to 500 '''billion''' yen ($3.6 billion) with support from the Japanese government.}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|date=2023-10-30|journal= Scientific Reports|volume=13|author=Herbold et al.|title=A large-scale comparison of human-written versus ChatGPT-generated essays|page=1|title_plain=18617|text=The ChatGPT service which serves as Web front-end to GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 was the fastest-growing service in history to break the 100 million user milestone in January and had 1 '''billion''' visits by February 2023.}}
##* {{quote-web|en|title=COMPLAINT FOR DECLARATORY AND INJUNCTIVE RELIEF|url=https://www.justsecurity.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/new-york-v-trump-doge-treasury-feb-7-2025.pdf|date=2025-02-08|page=2|work=w:United States District Court for the Southern District of New York|passage=Plaintiff States also receive '''billions''' of dollars in funds every year directly from Treasury through BFS under federal grant programs.}}
## {{senseid|en|Q862978}} {{lb|en|dated|British & Australian|long scale}} A [[million]] (times a) [[million]] ({{w|Long and short scales#Comparison|logic: 1,000,000<sup>2</sup>}}): a 1 followed by twelve zeros (10<sup>12</sup>); a thousand milliard.
##: {{syn|en|trillion<id:Q862978><qq:[[short scale]]>}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|title=A Method of Finding, by the Help of Sir Isaac Newton's Binomial Theorem, a Near Value of the very Slowly Converging Infinite Series [...] |author=Francis Maseres|work=Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society |year=1778 |volume=lxviii  |issue=xli
|passage=''n'' = 1,000,000,000,000, that is, = a '''billion''', or the square of a million
|url=https://archive.org/details/philosophicaltra14royarich/page/452/mode/2up}}
##* {{quote-journal |en |work=Hansard |date=2000-11-08 |author=Stephen Ladyman |title=[Speech to the House of Commons]
|passage=There is a bill to be picked up for cleaning the former Soviet countries of £1 '''billion'''. By that I mean a British '''billion''', because when I was little I was told that a '''billion''' was a million million and then the Americans said that it was a thousand million. Well, I am talking about a million million pounds worth of clean-up to be done.
|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2000-11-08/debates/d6ed870b-be63-43fb-aead-8d1ae18eb568/CommonsChamber#contribution-746507c2-9e31-49a8-ba61-482a48eb884e}}
