===Etymology===
From {{af|fr|bi-|gloss1=two|-illion}}; [[i.e.]], a [[million]] [[million]].

Coined by {{w|Jehan Adam}} in 1475 as '''by-million'''.<ref name="genevieve">Bibliothèque St Geneviève, Paris, MS Français 3143 - original French manuscript by Jehan Adam</ref> <ref name="parchemin">{{cite-web |url=http://www-bsg.univ-paris1.fr/la_reserve/expos/sciences/savants2.htm |title=Jehan Adam, Traicté en arismetique pour la practique par gectouers… Parchemin. XVe siècle (1475). |accessdate=3 July 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930165302/http://www-bsg.univ-paris1.fr/la_reserve/expos/sciences/savants2.htm |archivedate=30 September 2007 }}</ref> <ref name="thorndike">Lynn Thorndike, “The Arithmetic of Jehan Adam, A.D. 1475,” Science and Thought in the Fifteenth Century</ref>
Rendered as '''byllion''' by {{w|Nicolas Chuquet}} in 1484, in his article “Triparty en la science des nombres”.<ref name="Chuquet1">
{{cite-book|last=Chuquet
|first=Nicolas
|title=Triparty en la science des nombres (ISSN 9012-9458)
|publisher=Aristide Marre
|location=Bologna (Italy)
|year_published=1880
|year=1484
}}
